											<td width="100%" valign="top">					
												<!-- START NEWS AREAS-->
												<table width="90%" border="0" align="center" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
													<tr><td valign="top" width="100%">&nbsp;<br>
													<!-- strMainData goes here-->
													<table align='center' cellpadding=5 width='85%'>  <tr><td class='header' bgcolor='black' width='100%'>PALADIN STRATEGIES AND PLAYGUIDES</td></tr>  <tr><td width='100%' class='db'><font class='spti'>PALADINS.. AMONG THE BEST 3 PVP CLASSES THERE ARE.</font> - <small>Mabwen Winterlite, Solusek Ro</td></tr>
  <tr><td width='100%' class='db'>At your lower levels, around 9-20 you arent that great at PvP, becuase your spells are still weak until about level 22. Paladins are pretty much feared in duels, i mean a blinding, rooting, stunning tank? a good way to take out each class in a duel is listed below, i have learned these from experience:
<P>
WARRIOR - Forget about root, its useless, your main spell in this duel is blind. Blind them and step behind them therefore you will be hitting them and they will not hit back. if they run.. then use root, stun helps out just a little if they are duel wielding, but if 2h use it a lot. Use lay hands at about 1/4 a bubble of health 
<P>
WIZARD - They are among the easiest class. Dont worry about Blinds, unless you are in the lower levels, becuase most high level wizards have their spells macroed and it doesnt make a differance, they dont tank. Root them, bash them when they start to cast, and stun them as well. use lay hands at about 1 bubble of health left.
<P>
DRUID - They tend to try and kite you. Prevent this by blinding them.. they cant run and cast macroed spells at the same time, that is if they are macroed. Make sure they are blinded alot and if they start to run and cast on you. Stand still, dont chase them if you havent used your lay hands yet, if you have, GET THEM!!!! =) and dont use lay hands unless you have 1 bubble of health left.
<P>
NECROMANCER - This is the ONE class i have the most trouble dueling with. They will use all of their mana on you, let you use lay hands and then run away from you. They then meditate and come back and your through. To prevent this you must first get rid of that annoying pet they have. Fear Vs. Undead does wonders. if it isnt memmed and he is attacking you use blind and step away from him. Now as for the necro, keep your eye on him at all time, make sure you never go below a bubble of mana. When he starts to run, stop him with a stun (if you can) then stand next to him and root. then tank im hehe. When the necromancer falls so does the pet so just keep it feared and you will be fine.
<P>
MAGICIAN - the other very hard class.. their earth pet can really get to you. Use blind on their pet AT THE FIRST PART OF THE DUEL, i cant stress this enough, if you attack him to much, he will get really provoked on you and you cant use your blind to make him run. When you blind him he will keep attacking, just take a step back. Whats that say, you cant? your rooted? aww just stun the ele and wait for root to wear. Watch the magician however, if he is foolish enough to start meditating, prevent it by shooting an arrow >=) keep the pet away from you and root the magician, their spells arent that strong so it shouldint be that tough.
<P>
ENCHANTER - A formidable foe, if you dont know how to take care of them. Rune is a powerfull spell, so whenever they start to buff INTERUPPT!!!! make sure they dont pull off that many spells, the best way to deal with this is to cary an egg shaped pumice and if they charm you, use it =) you wont be charmed. God help us they wont send you at a guard if you are charmed. make sure when he/she is casting the spell with the green stuff, interuppt them the most. The pets arent that strong, so just blind them and step back like you deal with all the pets. make sure they dont keep casting rune, becuase in most cases rune is better than heal.
<P>
RANGER - Same as warrior except keep them rooted, their DD's can sometimes do enough damage to get you, and if they snare you and attempt to kite you, stop
<P>
SHAMAN - They run out of mana, they CANT kill you you have to many hps with LOH. Egg shaped pumice can help a lot, let them cast all their dots and waste mana, then just use it and get rid o em all. =). basically keep them rooted and stunned. Their pets you can bild however it doesnt last long so i would suggest rooting then attacking the shaman, its always easiest to pull off a root when the target is stunned, keep that in mind. Otherwise, treat them like any other caster and take out the trash =)
<P>
ROGUE - They seem to spin around you a LOT, so stun helps you out a lot, if you dont got it watch it and keep em rooted, if you dont have root or stun you shouldint be in this duel in the first place. Keep your face to them and when they start to spin around you and you are out of mana, start to run from them and they will chase you in a strait line, turn around occasionally and turn on auto attack, assuming you run away without auto attack on, but they have very few hps but may be a challenge if your not carefull, if the turning around doesnt work just run from them till you have enough mana for a root or stun.
<P>
SHADOWKNIGHT - Watch their Harm touch, if they dont use it at first you may be in trouble. They tend to get some of their brothers cowardice, running when you already have used LOH but they dont have the best spells in the world and unless they have a manastone or a clarity you will be alright, if they use harm touch at first, use loh at about 1/4 a bub of health, if they havent used it at first, use loh at 1 and 1/2 bubbles of health, otherwise you wouldint be able to use it at all. dont worry about pets they are to low level to make a big impact but if it really bothers you, fear em
<P>
IN GENERAL- Keep the pets away with blind and fear vs undead (necros and Sks) dont try any of that fancy footwork either, it will backfire and the other guy will start as well and you will just see two guys prettymuch dancing. Rogues and warriors can do that because most of their weapons have low delay, if they start any of that on you keep em rooted.


		</td></tr>
